value:
Comprising beaker, spice box, knife, fork, and spoon, with detachable handles engraved with foliate scrolls. The beaker further engraved with a monogram within a circular cartouche supported by two angels; on the opposite side is an engraved figure of a man with a hawk in his hand.  The base is engraved "The Guift of The Honorable Lady Tipping ye April 15 1708". 
Wooden case covered in shagreen, with a lining of green velvet and silver binding

summary_title: Treasured Possessions from the Renaissance to the Enlightenment
